    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Margaret McGorman Berry (1880-?) was an American poet.  Born September 20, 1880, she was 
	  educated in Canadian grammar schools and later in the United States.  Prior to her marriage she wrote under 
	  her maiden name, M. M. Lamb.  She was active in poetry associations in Virginia, New York, and New Jersey.  
	  Her poems appeared in national magazines such as <emph render="italic">The Bard</emph>, <emph render="italic">Blue Moon</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Lantern</emph>, <emph render="italic">Saturday Evening Post</emph> 
	  and several small poetry magazines as well as various newspapers.  A collection of her poems, <emph render="italic">Harnessed Dreams</emph>, 
	  was published in 1951, and her work has also appeared in many anthologies.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Margaret McGorman Berry Papers</emph> consist of a subject file, correspondence, manuscripts, and published 
	  material.  The <emph render="bold">Subject file</emph> contains an unpublished guide to her work including an index to her poems and 
	  a list of publications in which her work appeared.  <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph>, dated 1946-1951, contains incoming 
	  letters only.  <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> include unpublished poems in both typescript and handwritten form, a partial manuscript 
	  of her book, Harnessed Dreams, and the text of a speech.  <emph render="bold">Published material</emph> includes tear sheets of her poems 
	  from various journals, her book, a catalog in which she is mentioned, and a selection of newspaper clippings 
	  about her.</p>
    </scopecontent>
